Using UNION ALL for Different Transaction Types: You could write separate queries for each transaction type (e.g., one for Sales Posted, one for Purchase Posted, one for Nominal Posted) and combine their results using UNION ALL. However, this requires careful column alignment. Fields not available for a specific type would need to be selected as NULL or an empty string to match the columns from other queries. This still wouldn't solve the issue of linking sub-ledger transactions directly to their Nominal postings in a single row, as those links aren't physical.
